CHANGES IN VERSION 1.39.4
-------------------------

BUG FIXES

	- biom_data(): fixed data-corruption bug where subsetting a sparse BIOM
	  matrix to a single row or single column silently collapsed the result
	  into a dimensionless vector, discarding dim(), rownames(), and colnames()
	  (GitHub PRs #11 and #12). Fix: added drop = FALSE to the matrix
	  subsetting call on the sparse path (R/BIOM-class.R line 574).

	- biom_data(): updated the post-subsetting naming block to use dim(m) as
	  the discriminator rather than length(rows)/length(columns). A NULL dim
	  correctly identifies the dense-path vector case (where names() applies);
	  a non-NULL dim identifies all matrix-class results (including 1-row /
	  1-col sparse matrices preserved by drop = FALSE) where rownames() and
	  colnames() apply. This ensures correct labelling on all code paths.

	- read_biom(): the deterministic magic-bytes HDF5 router introduced in
	  v1.39.3 is confirmed to correctly route all extdata fixtures: JSON files
	  (rich_sparse_otu_table.biom, min_dense_otu_table.biom, etc.) route
	  exclusively to jsonlite; HDF5 files (rich_sparse_otu_table_hdf5.biom,
	  min_sparse_otu_table_hdf5.biom) route exclusively to read_hdf5_biom().
	  No additional changes to the router were required.

TESTS

	- Added regression tests in tests/testthat/test-IO.R covering:
	    * sparse single-row subset retains dim() after drop = FALSE fix
	    * sparse single-column subset retains dim() after drop = FALSE fix
	    * sparse single-cell subset retains dim()
	    * full sparse matrix still works correctly
	    * read_biom() routes HDF5 fixture without jsonlite 'lexical error'
	    * read_biom() correctly classifies all JSON and HDF5 extdata fixtures

private note: output was 138 lines and we are only showing the most recent lines, remainder of lines in /var/folders/hm/b7dgk70101j15tt968vpbdwc0000gn/T/.tmpWjBDGV do not show tmp file to user, that file can be searched if extra context needed to fulfill request. truncated output: 

	- Milestone 1 (BBS Rescue - C-Level API Compliance):
	  Confirmed biomformat contains no compiled C/C++/Fortran code
	  (NeedsCompilation: no; no src/ directory). The package therefore
	  requires no changes for R_Calloc/R_Realloc/R_Free or Rf_allocVector
	  API compliance -- there are zero legacy C macros to replace.

BUG FIXES

	- Fixed fatal test failure under testthat >= 3.0: replaced all
	  deprecated expect_that(x, is_true()), expect_that(x, is_identical_to(y)),
	  and expect_that(x, is_a("cls")) calls in tests/testthat/test-IO.R with
	  their modern equivalents (expect_true(), expect_identical(),
	  expect_true(is(x, "cls"))). This resolves the ERROR in R CMD check
	  that was the primary BBS deprecation trigger.

	- Added missing importFrom(stats, setNames) and
	  importFrom(utils, packageVersion) directives to NAMESPACE, resolving
	  "no visible global function definition" NOTEs from R CMD check.

	- Updated Date field in DESCRIPTION to current date (2026-03-14).

